# Python Azure Functions - Local Settings Example

Copy this file to `local.settings.json` and fill in your actual values.

```json
{
  "IsEncrypted": false,
  "Values": {
    "AzureWebJobsStorage": "UseDevelopmentStorage=true",
    "FUNCTIONS_WORKER_RUNTIME": "python",
    "AzureWebJobsDashboard": "UseDevelopmentStorage=true",
    
    "SUPABASE_JWT_SECRET": "your-supabase-jwt-secret-here",
    
    "COSMOS_DB_ENDPOINT": "https://your-account.documents.azure.com:443/",
    "COSMOS_DB_KEY": "your-cosmos-db-primary-key-here",
    "COSMOS_DB_DATABASE": "PostsDB",
    "COSMOS_DB_CONTAINER": "posts"
  },
  "Host": {
    "CORS": {
      "AllowCredentials": false,
      "AllowedOrigins": [
        "http://localhost:5173",
        "http://localhost:3000",
        "https://yourdomain.azurewebsites.net"
      ],
      "AllowedMethods": [
        "GET",
        "POST",
        "PUT",
        "DELETE",
        "OPTIONS"
      ],
      "AllowedHeaders": [
        "Content-Type",
        "Authorization",
        "X-Requested-With"
      ],
      "MaxAge": 3600
    }
  },
  "functionTimeout": "00:05:00"
}
```

## How to Use

1. Rename this file to `local.settings.json` in the `python-function` directory
2. Replace the placeholder values with your actual credentials
3. DO NOT commit this file to version control (add to .gitignore)
4. Run your Function App with `func start`

## Required Secrets

See [ENV_VARIABLES_GUIDE.md](./ENV_VARIABLES_GUIDE.md) for detailed instructions on finding these values.
